              "id": "glog-a840cac5-ef4b-48cc-8dca-1750065a0343",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "### Description\n\nIn C++ programming, storing sensitive information such as tokens or keys directly within the source code can lead to significant security vulnerabilities. If the source code is exposed, either through a version control system, a code leak, or reverse engineering, attackers can easily access these sensitive credentials. This can lead to unauthorized access to systems, data breaches, and other security incidents.\n\n### General Mitigation Advice\n\n1. **Environment Variables**: Store sensitive information in environment variables instead of hardcoding them in the source code.\n2. **Configuration Files**: Use configuration files that are not included in the source code repository. Ensure these files are encrypted or access-controlled.\n3. **Secrets Management Tools**: Utilize secrets management tools like HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or Azure Key Vault to securely store and access sensitive information.\n4. **Access Control**: Limit access to the source code and configuration files to only those who need it.\n5. **Code Reviews**: Regularly conduct code reviews to ensure that sensitive information is not being stored in the source code.\n\n### Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\n#### Vulnerability Sink\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n#include <string>\n\nint main() {\n    // Vulnerable: Hardcoded API token\n    std::string apiToken = \"304aab1d359c295d2740970311b943771af944f67432e719df628fe77b61\";\n    std::cout << \"API Token: \" << apiToken << std::endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\n#### Fixed Code\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n#include <string>\n#include <cstdlib> // For getenv\n\nint main() {\n    // Mitigation: Retrieve API token from environment variable\n    const char* apiToken = std::getenv(\"API_TOKEN\");\n    if (apiToken == nullptr) {\n        std::cerr << \"Error: API token not set in environment variables.\" << std::endl;\n        return 1;\n    }\n    std::cout << \"API Token: \" << apiToken << std::endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\n### Library Dependencies\n\n- Standard C++ library (`<iostream>`, `<string>`)\n- C Standard Library (`<cstdlib>` for `getenv` function)\n\n### OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top Ten](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [OWASP Cheat Sheet Series: Secrets Management](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Secrets_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n### Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
