              "id": "glog-1af71a2b-5684-437b-8eb5-64096db9dddd",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "### Description\n\nIn C++ programming, storing sensitive information such as tokens or keys directly in the source code is a common vulnerability. This practice can lead to unauthorized access if the source code is exposed, as attackers can easily extract these secrets. This vulnerability is particularly dangerous in environments where the source code is shared or stored in version control systems.\n\n### General Mitigation Advice\n\n1. **Environment Variables**: Store sensitive information in environment variables instead of hardcoding them in the source code.\n2. **Configuration Files**: Use configuration files that are not included in the source code repository to store sensitive data. Ensure these files are encrypted or access-controlled.\n3. **Secret Management Tools**: Utilize secret management tools like HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or Azure Key Vault to securely store and access sensitive information.\n4. **Access Control**: Implement strict access control measures to ensure that only authorized personnel can access sensitive information.\n5. **Code Reviews**: Conduct regular code reviews to identify and remove any hardcoded secrets.\n\n### Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nBelow is an example of how to refactor code to avoid storing tokens or keys directly in the source code:\n\n#### Vulnerable Code\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n\nint main() {\n    // Vulnerable: Hardcoded API token\n    std::string apiToken = \"b751850b1a57168a5693cd924b6b096e08f621827444f70d884f5d0240d2712e10e1\";\n    std::cout << \"API Token: \" << apiToken << std::endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\n#### Fixed Code\n\n```cpp\n#include <iostream>\n#include <cstdlib> // Required for getenv\n\nint main() {\n    // Mitigation: Retrieve API token from environment variable\n    const char* apiToken = std::getenv(\"API_TOKEN\");\n    if (apiToken == nullptr) {\n        std::cerr << \"Error: API token not set in environment variables.\" << std::endl;\n        return 1;\n    }\n    std::cout << \"API Token: \" << apiToken << std::endl;\n    return 0;\n}\n```\n\n### Library Dependencies\n\n- Standard C++ Library\n- `<cstdlib>` for `getenv` function\n\n### OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP Top Ten](https://owasp.org/www-project-top-ten/)\n- [OWASP Cheat Sheet Series: Secrets Management](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Secrets_Management_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n### Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/798.html)"
